author: James Ramage
title: Dollar Weakens Ahead of Fed Minutes
text:
The dollar fell against the euro and yen on Wednesday ahead of the release of minutes by the Federal Reserve’s policy-making group on concerns that they may not provide much clarity to the interest-rate picture.
The dollar declined 0.4% against the common currency, as one euro bought $1.1064. The U.S. currency slid 0.3% versus the yen to ¥124.10.
